  <!-- Safety Section -->
  <section class="section-bone">
    <h2>Are Bone Conduction Headphones & Earphones Safe for Your Ears?</h2>
    <p>Yes! Bone conduction headphones and earphones are<strong>FDA-approved</strong> and reduce ear canal damage risk since they don't blast sound directly into your eardrum. However, excessive volume can still cause bone vibration discomfort.</p>
    <p>In fact, they're considered <strong>one of the safest audio devices</strong> available today. Because they don't go inside your ears, they reduce the risk of:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong><a href="https://ngearsafe.com/blogs/open-ear-headphones/ear-infection">Ear infections</a></strong></li>
      <li><strong>Hearing fatigue</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Eardrum damage</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <p>They're especially recommended for kids, older adults, and anyone using headphones for long hours.</p>
  </section>

